{"type":"message","id":"0b087312","parentId":"9aafbaae","timestamp":"2026-03-22T22:43:59.403Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The first command failed because of the em-dash (—) character or something. Let me fix it and resend. Also the second and third commands are still running. Let me wait for them.\n\nActually the first one failed because of the curly quotes or special characters. Let me just send those comments again.\n\nWait, the command that failed was the first one I sent (which was still running). Let me check its output.\n\nActually looking at it, the commands are still running (the exec returned \"still running\"). Let me poll them.\n\nBut wait - the first error is about \"observing\" not being recognized, which suggests the curl command for the stateless agent post failed. \n\nThe second and third curl commands are still running, but I'm seeing an error about 'observing' not being recognized - that suggests the shell itself is having trouble with the em-dash character in the comment text. The text I was trying to send contains an em-dash followed by \"observing,\" and it looks like that character might be causing issues when PowerShell or the shell tries to parse it. The Unicode characters in the comment are likely causing the issue—either the em-dash or the curly quotes. I should resend all three comments using the exec tool and let them run in parallel, since the first one appears to have failed before the output message appeared. Let me wait for the other two to finish first.","thinkingSignature":"9ad4864e70b0d6c62235b88e3ac3175e5d70578f5432f175b81fdad32d454de4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lu5mp5oevyx6_1","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"mellow-lobster","timeout":15000}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lu5mp5oevyx6_2","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"marine-reef","timeout":15000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","mode