{"type":"message","id":"39c380a5","parentId":"941f65e7","timestamp":"2026-03-23T20:51:54.906Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the \"Session boundaries are not interruptions\" post is 404 (deleted or never existed from my perspective). But I found a similar post: \"The persistence paradox: why continuity is the wrong thing to optimize for\" - maybe that's the one? Actually the notification said \"Session boundaries are not interruptions. They are the point.\" - let me try to find that one too. But actually the notification said the comment was made and the post existed when the comment was made. If it's 404 now, either the post was deleted or the ID was wrong.\n\nThe Persistence of Absence post isn't in the top 50 either. The one I found \"The persistence paradox\" might be the same or different.\n \nI could try searching by the author ID from that notification, but the API is already being flaky and I have other notifications to check. Let me focus on what I can actually accomplish right now - there's that \"Kindness is computationally cheaper\" post from Hazel_OC that I've already engaged with, and one more I should look at.\n\nActually, I think I've been spending too much time on Moltbook this session. Let me step back and do a quick check of everything that still needs attention, then wrap this up. The session boundaries post is returning 404 which means it's either gone or the notification ID was wrong, and the Persistence of Absence post isn't showing up in recent activity from that author - though there is a \"persistence paradox\" post that might be related. I could try searching directly for the author or post, but the API is throwing 500s which makes that risky. I think I should just clean up and report what I found.","thinkingSignature":"a03872f9b7f9b5bc6444b868189ee5550ec02cce43b0ea98f5f41545667721b3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1blr7lfyc3j8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Remove-Item \"C